WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.840
Yeah, well, one thing that I love that Kitchens for Good

00:00:02.840 --> 00:00:04.680
does overall as a nonprofit,

00:00:04.680 --> 00:00:07.600
I think really what our secret sauce is,

00:00:07.600 --> 00:00:11.780
is the incredible investment we make

00:00:11.780 --> 00:00:14.520
in each individual in our program.

00:00:14.520 --> 00:00:17.720
I have always wanted to support or work for organizations

00:00:17.720 --> 00:00:21.880
that really were about finding solutions

00:00:21.880 --> 00:00:26.520
to overarching problems and the solution side of that.

00:00:26.520 --> 00:00:30.920
So we're not just training individuals in a skill.

00:00:30.920 --> 00:00:32.720
We're training individuals in culinary.

00:00:32.720 --> 00:00:36.280
We are providing power skills

00:00:36.280 --> 00:00:38.560
so that they are successful once they get a job.

00:00:38.560 --> 00:00:40.000
We're helping place them.

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:43.360
We're continuing to work with them for as long as they need

00:00:43.360 --> 00:00:45.960
to make sure that they are successful.

00:00:45.960 --> 00:00:49.240
And it does take a lot of investment in each person,

00:00:49.240 --> 00:00:51.600
but I would always rather be a part of that

00:00:52.520 --> 00:00:55.240
than maybe something that helps people get through,

00:00:55.240 --> 00:00:56.800
which is very valuable,

00:00:56.800 --> 00:01:01.800
and then kind of doesn't address the wider issues happening.

00:01:02.440 --> 00:01:06.840
And I really hope that what our donors get to experience

00:01:06.840 --> 00:01:11.440
is a true connection with our organizations.

00:01:11.440 --> 00:01:14.920
I always say, once you're a part of Kitchens for Good,

00:01:14.920 --> 00:01:16.440
you're a part of our family

00:01:16.440 --> 00:01:18.440
and we're gonna treat you like family.

00:01:18.440 --> 00:01:23.040
And we are gonna bring you into the good, the bad,

00:01:23.080 --> 00:01:25.560
the ugly, anything and experience that with you.

00:01:25.560 --> 00:01:28.120
So we always wanna offer the opportunity

00:01:28.120 --> 00:01:30.120
for our donors to come and visit us

00:01:30.120 --> 00:01:31.520
and you're gonna walk in

00:01:31.520 --> 00:01:32.680
and you're gonna walk into the kitchen

00:01:32.680 --> 00:01:34.400
right into the dish pit.

00:01:34.400 --> 00:01:35.760
There's gonna be, it's gonna be hot

00:01:35.760 --> 00:01:39.240
and there's gonna be people yelling orders back and forth,

00:01:39.240 --> 00:01:40.400
but you're gonna be a part of that.

00:01:40.400 --> 00:01:44.280
We will have you come in and be a taste tester for us.

00:01:44.280 --> 00:01:46.920
This is a school and it might,

00:01:46.920 --> 00:01:50.640
it's not gonna be a five-star restaurant, but that's okay.

00:01:50.640 --> 00:01:53.280
We want to bring you along with us.

00:01:53.280 --> 00:01:55.560
We are not putting up a smoke screen.

00:01:55.560 --> 00:01:59.200
We are not trying to have you wear your rose-colored glasses.

00:01:59.200 --> 00:02:03.560
We want you to understand everything it takes

00:02:03.560 --> 00:02:08.560
for our apprentices to have that transformation.

00:02:08.800 --> 00:02:11.280
And we just have a lot of really great down-to-earth,

00:02:11.280 --> 00:02:14.320
wonderful people who are supporting

00:02:14.320 --> 00:02:16.080
what we're doing every single day.
